main event: Sightings of bright, round objects over Boston Harbor, Massachusetts reported on October 25, 1960.
interesting points: Objects moved erratically and maneuvered independently,Objects became slightly obscured by clouds multiple times,Objects were visually observed and also tracked by ground radar,Radar indicated speeds in excess of 700 mph with a disappearance speed of over 1000 mph,The objects appeared to be a dull white color at times.
sighted object: four to seven bright, round objects
witness description: Civilian report, verified by Air Force.
